    "body": "> I have used 3,000,000 gas limit. \r\n\r\nYes, on the outer transaction. The solidity-construct `transfer` does a `CALL` under the hood, and that `CALL` only has enough gas for outputting a log. It does not forward all gas, to prevent re-entrancy problems. `transfer` also handles error-conditions, so that if the `CALL` (transfer of ether) is unsuccessfull, it throws. ",
